cisions. Looking at section s2, I need to verify the request message specification is fully captured - checking the header record structure at 50 bytes and the data record at 420 bytes, along with all the individual fields listed in each section. I'm verifying the remaining mobile phone fields against the knowledge base specifications. The local number and subscription number fields both require half-width digits with a 4-digit maximum, and they're conditionally mandatory depending on whether the area code is filled in. The FILLER2 field completes the validation checklist.\n\nNow moving into section s3, I'm checking the response message specifications. The header record is 50 bytes with all required items accounted for, and the data record is 420 bytes containing the record type, user ID, error reason code, inquiry ID, and filler. The processing result and error reason code table has all four rows present.\n\nI'm starting to verify section s1 against the source documentation to check for any discrepancies. Looking at the section structure, the knowledge file correctly captures the three main h2-level sections from the source. Now I'm checking whether the hints in s1 are actually supported by the source content — \"MOMメッセージング\" appears to be inferred from the file path and context rather than explicitly stated in the document itself, which is a minor stretch but reasonable given the file organization. I'm verifying the message IDs are all captured in the hints, which they are. But I'm noticing a key implementation detail that's missing from the hints: the sample application implements the message sending logic in the action handler for the send button on the user registration confirmation screen, and this is where the user registration message transmission gets triggered.\n\nFor the fabrication concerns, the hint \"MOMメッセージング\" isn't explicitly stated in the source material—it's inferred from context. Similarly, \"同期メッセージ送信\" describes the synchronous message sending